Crypto.description:
Red is one of the most recognizable colors of the Roman Empire, associated with the Mars, the God of War. Red banners would be raised during celebrations of military victories. However, something seems off with this banner...

Each word in the flag should be separated by an underscore. Make sure not to yell when typing in the flag.

Developed by: [N00D135](https://github.com/Iamironman15)
hints: Hidden in a famous fast food restaurant, a historic display is dedicated to the talkers who mastered this code.
Crypto.name: twisted-tongues

Crypto.description:
My greek friend recently has been screwing around with the idea of cryptography and sent me a message. Can you tell me what here message says?

Format: `nicc{theanswer}`

Developed by: [TomB](https://www.github.com/Tomaszbrauntsch/)
Crypto.name: My-friend's-message

Crypto.description:
As you venture through The Bibliotheca, a renowned repository of ancient texts and knowledge, you stumble upon a forgotten corner obscured by dust and neglect. Between two towering tomes of myth and legend, you uncover a piece of sheet music, delicately wedged as if hidden for centuries. Its faded parchment bears no title, no composer's name, only a cryptic message scrawled hastily in the margins: "Read the secrets". Uncover the hidden message, the gods have blessed you, the 3rd beat in the 3rd measure is N.

Submit the flag in the format `nicc{flag_message}`

Developed by: [tkg1121](https://github.com/tkg1121)
hints: The theme is music
Crypto.name: Symphony-of-Secrets
the-receiver-of-many

Crypto.description:
Zeus is throwing the party of eons at the The Gardens of the Hesperides!!! Hermes is going to pick you up, but in order to get in you need to tell him the passcode or he's gonna leave you stranded! You have no idea what the passcode is, but you have a drinking cup, a party gift from the last one. Take a look at it, maybe there's a clue on it on what the password was. It belonged to an oracle that got so drunk, they went on a vision spell way into the future and started tweaking out!! They were biting into their cup, making clicky noises, scratching into it, rubbing the paint off. Look at the thing! It barely held up.

Flag format: `nicc{flag}`

Developed by: [rickyhernandez1000](https://github.com/rickyhernandez1000)
hints: Look closely at the cup.
Crypto.name: Party-at-the-Gardens

Crypto.description:
* We received a copy of a painting today that was given to The Council.
* It seems to be a copy of The Fall of Atlantis by the artist François de Nomé.
* Scribbled on the back of the painting was a message that read:

```Those who wander are lost.
Those who gather are found.
Those who seek are blind.
Those who see are bound.

To help hide our home,
we sought to deceive,
And told those who roam,
that we were lost to the seas.

Only when you eXamine `truth of time`
bY `LIES FROM OLD` 
Will you find the map
To our home of gold.
```

This is probably nothing... right?

Developed by: [Cyb0rgSw0rd](https://github.com/alfredsimpson)
Crypto.name: fine-art

Forensics.description:
In the vast expanse of digital space, an enigmatic anomaly has emerged, drawing upon the timeless tales of gods and monsters. It is known simply as the Event Horizon, a mysterious threshold where the boundaries between myth and reality blur. Will you dare to venture into the depths of the Event Horizon and uncover the mythic echoes that reverberate within? The fate of the digital realm and the legacy of ancient legends await those brave enough to embark on this epic quest. Find the suspicious event and send the time of its creation as the flag.

The format should be in the format `nicc{XXXX-XX-XXTXX:XX:XX.XXXXXXXZ}`

Developed by: [tkg1121](https://github.com/tkg1121)
hints: UTC time
Forensics.name: Event-Horizon

* Input the Flag as follows `nicc{movie,movie}` continue commas for more movies as found.

OSINT.description:
Somewhere far in the South East, a hero from three centuries ago wrote up a manuscript. It detailed how practicioners from their era should deal with the afflicted. Some say the affliction is incurable as if a spell were cast on them. Unfortunately, this national hero would later be executed for some of his other writings. I wonder if you can help me find the name of this manuscript?

Flag should be the name of the paper in its untranslated form, with each word separated by a '-'. Diacritics or accent marks on letters are not required.

Example: `nicc{Of-Mice-and-Men}`

Developed by: BonsaiUmai
hints: Colonizers of the country executed this individual
OSINT.name: Witchcraft-in-the-South-East

OSINT.description:
Simon Letti got lost in time again... 

Unfortunately, his professor refused to let him go see the Eclipse. He was so excited, too! Apparently his professor thought it wasn't worth it since NJIT wasn't going to get a total eclipse.

He was so upset he decided he was going to mix two of his favorite things: space and ancient civilizations. Maybe he's been watching too much Stargate?

He wouldn't say where he was going, but he was supposed to check in with Anna every 24 hours so we know he was safe but it's been a week already! 

If we can find out when and where he was going we can probably go back and save him!

His dorm had a message on the door:


> Anna, 
> Prof was right - we weren't going to see it fully here... 
> But I found the perfect eclipse! 
> 
> It was just over 𝋥 long at the Kukulkan's Castle! 
> And it's brand new, so it'll be awesome.
> Can you tell I've been practicing their language so I can communicate when I'm there? 
> They talk in numbers, right?
> Anyway, I'll see ya back in 𝋥𝋫𝋤 -- hopefully!
> 
> Don't worry, I'll check in!
> 
> - Simon


If we can find the date of the eclipse and where he was going, we can probably get him back in time for the fall semester!

flag format: `nicc{YYYY-MM-DD_City-Name}`
**You can ignore any accents on the city name, if there are any. We'll figure it out!**


* Developed by:	 [Cyb0rgSw0rd](https://github.com/AlfredSimpson)
OSINT.name: I don't want to be a sacrifice!

Web.description:
Cast into the inferno's depths, souls languish in perpetual torment, with no reprieve from the hellfire's embrace. Yet whispers endure of a realm_key, a legendary artifact able to traverse the boundaries between worlds, offering a glimmer of salvation. The question that burns as fiercely as the flames themselves: do you possess the courage to seek it? Find flag.txt and submit the flag in the format flag nicc{flag}


Developed by: [tkg1121](https://github.com/tkg1121)
hints: The Keeper's Riddle last line
Web.name: Underworld-Bypass

Web.description:
In the realm of digital Olympus, the Socratic-Script guarded its gates with cunning riddles. Only those versed in wisdom's tongue could unlock its secrets and ascend to the summit of victory. Many seekers faltered, but the chosen few, armed with knowledge, triumphed over the enigmatic challenge, earning their place among the digital deities. Upon your arrival, you discover an ancient tome with writing, what could it mean? Submit the flag found after gaining passage.

`nicc{flag}`

Developed by: [tkg1121](https://github.com/tkg1121)
hints: Challenge would be so much easier if that filter was not there huh
Web.name: Socratic-Script

Web.description:
A few months ago, we found a control panel for a time machine sitting openly on the Internet. Since then, it has been upgraded to require authentication with a username and password. Can you find a way to get in?

Developed by: [Noah Jacobson](https://github.com/noahajac)
hints: How do you interact with a database?
What does your browser see when requesting web pages?

Whether she was Hesiod's disfigured monstrous mortal or Ovid's cursed and abused fair maiden--Medusa and her Gorgon sisters must be stopped. If not we shall all be turned to stone! Enter their lair, learn your surroundings, and find a way...

Developed by: [machoG](https://www.reddit.com/r/ClassicalEducation/comments/qveh4m/medusa_by_me_digital_discussion_hesiod_vs_ovids)
hints: INSPECTION is the key.

Web.description:
Great job gaining access to the site! We managed to get a hold of some of the code that's making the site work. The source that provided us the code also told us that the time machine's owner is trying to go back in time to find Koalemos. Why? Who knows! That isn't important right now.

The time machine currently does not appear to be working. I'm not saying it's a refrigerator box...but it's totally a refrigerator box.

Anyways, we think there is still some information hidden on the server. Can you find how to get it it?

Developed by: [Noah Jacobson](https://github.com/noahajac)
hints: [object Object]
Web.name: back-in-time-2-electric-boogaloo
